boxesnonce','634086b3fa'),(1135,105,'post_title','Dancing\'s for the Dogs (and Cats)!!!!'),(1136,105,'samplepermalinknonce','b0757bed0a'),(1137,105,'content','<a href=\"http://blog.adltexas.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/dancings.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-108\" title=\"dancings\" src=\"http://blog.adltexas.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/dancings-300x231.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"231\" /></a>Boy oh boy am I excited about this one!  A local dance studio is hosting a donation drive for the Animal Defense League this Friday and it\'s going to be a blast!  I am by no means Ginger Rogers, but I LOVE to dance!!!  You know when Eliza Dolittle sings \"I Could Have Dance All Night?\"  That\'s me, without the cockney accent though.  Or how about when Gene Kelly yells \"Gotta Dance!!!\" in \"Singing in the Rain?\" Yeah, I\'ve done that ... in the rain!  The bad thing is I have no rhythm ... zip, zero, zilch.  it goes well with my two left feet.  So what!?!?!  It\'s fun and YOLO, right?  So now I get to combine one of my favorite hobbies with my favorite mission, helping the dogs and cats at the AD.  The Wanda Deagen Studio at 2113 Vance Jackson is hosting a benefit this Friday, October 12th from 8 p.m. to 10 p.m.  Everyone is invited to attend ... just bring a donation off of the ADL wish list (or a monetary donation if you prefer).  You will get Merengue lesson followed by open dancing to a variety of music.  From the two-step tot he waltz to the cha-cha, you can try it all and make some new friends while helping the ADL.  Don\'t be afraid to boogie, even if you have two left feet (like me)!  This is for fun and no one is here to judge!  Wanda says she expects lots of people to be there, so we may use the parking lot and the studio for the event.  Dress casually, no tuxes or sweeping waltz dresses required!  You can bring the kids, too ... as long as they participate in the dancing as well.  Hey, if I can get out there and do it, so can you.  Plus, we can always tell ourselves it\'s all for the dogs, right?!?!?'),(1138,105,'save','Save Draft'),(1139,105,'wp-preview',''),(1140,105,'hidden_post_status','draft'),(1141,105,'post_status','publish'),(1142,105,'hidden_post_password',''),(1143,105,'hidden_post_visibility','public'),(1144,105,'visibility','public'),(1145,105,'post_password',''),(1146,105,'mm','10'),(1147,105,'jj','10'),(1148,105,'aa','2012'),(1149,105,'hh','12'),(1150,105,'mn','08'),(1151,105,'ss','52'),(1152,105,'hidden_mm','10'),(1153,105,'cur_mm','10'),(1154,105,'hidden_jj','10'),(1155,105,'cur_jj','10'),(1156,105,'hidden_aa','2012'),(1157,105,'cur_aa','2012'),(1158,105,'hidden_hh','12'),(1159,105,'cur_hh','12'),(1160,105,'hidden_mn','08'),(1161,105,'cur_mn','08'),(1162,105,'original_publish','Publish'),(1163,105,'post_format','0'),(1164,105,'post_category','a:2:{i:0;s:1:\"0\";i:1;s:2:\"17\";}'),(1165,105,'newcategory','New Category Name'),(1166,105,'newcategory_parent','-1'),(1167,105,'_ajax_nonce-add-category','9ce2c09bc0'),(1168,105,'tax_input','a:1:{s:8:\"post_tag\";s:34:\"Cat,Dance,Dog,Donate,Free,Merengue\";}'),(1169,105,'newtag','a:1:{s:8:\"post_tag\";s:0:\"\";}'),(1170,105,'excerpt',''),(1171,105,'trackback_url',''),(1172,105,'metakeyselect','#NONE#'),(1173,105,'metakeyinput',''),(1174,105,'metavalue',''),(1175,105,'_ajax_nonce-add-meta','2221c2866b'),(1176,105,'advanced_view','1'),(1177,105,'comment_status','open'),(1178,105,'ping_status','open'),(1179,105,'post_name',''),(1180,105,'post_author_override','2'),(1181,105,'pyre_overall_score','0'),(1182,105,'pyre_critera_1',''),(1183,105,'pyre_critera_1_score','0'),(1184,105,'pyre_critera_2',''),(1185,105,'pyre_critera_2_score','0'),(1186,105,'pyre_critera_3',''),(1187,105,'pyre_critera_3_score','0'),(1188,105,'pyre_critera_4',''),(1189,105,'pyre_critera_4_score','0'),(1190,105,'pyre_critera_5',''),(1191,105,'pyre_critera_5_score','0'),(1192,105,'post_mime_type',''),(1193,105,'ID','105'),(1194,105,'post_content','<a href=\"http://blog