INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (73,2,'2012-08-22 17:40:43','2012-08-22 22:40:43','<img class=\"wp-image-48 alignleft\" title=\"edison2\" src=\"http://blog.adltexas.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/edison2-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"275\" height=\"209\" />One of my favorite dogs here at ADL has finally found his forever home.  Edison had been here since January of this year.  He\'s a strikingly beautiful Dutch Shepherd mix with one blue eye.  My husband and I jokingly called him our \"Zombie Apocalypse\" dog because he just looked like the dog who would stick with you through anything.  Edison is one of the best.  He loves to run and play in water but will also just sit with you and relax.  It always made me scrtach my head wondering why he kept getting passed over by adopters.  Actually, that\'s not true ... I think I know exactly why he didn\'t get picked first.  Edison would be so excited to see someone when they got close to his kennel he would jump straight up into the air, which I think startled some people.  What they didn\'t know is that once you got him leashed and out of his kennel, he was by far one of the best walkers and calmest dogs you\'ll ever meet.  It just goes to show that first impressions aren\'t always the right ones.  If you\'re looking for a new best friend, give a dog a chance!  Really spend some quality time with the dog ... away from the kennels!  We have a lovely dog park for our dogs where you can spend 30 minutes (or more) to really get to know one another.  It will make all the difference in the world!  The man who adopted Edison found a real treasure of a dog and I am thrilled for both of them.  You can always check out the adult dogs and cats we have for adoption at <a href=\"http://adltexas.org/category/pets/\">adltexas.org</a>.  There are many more dogs just like Eddie waiting for someone to give them that second look and a second chance.','Give Them a Chance','','inherit','open','open','','46-revision-23','','','2012-08-22 17:40:43','2012-08-22 22:40:43','',46,'http://blog.adltexas.org/uncategorized/46-revision-23/',0,'revision','',0),(2,1,'2012-07-24 02:59:27','2012-07-24 02:59:27','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://blog.adltexas.org/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','publish','open','open','','sample-page','','','2012-07-24 02:59:27','2012-07-24 02:59:27','',0,'http://blog.adltexas.org/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(32,1,'2012-07-24 09:07:37','2012-07-24 14:07:37','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-25\" title=\"volunteer_2\" src=\"http://blog.adltexas.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/volunteer_2-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />There is no doubt that the volunteers at the Animal Defense League are more than just “helpers.” From walking dogs to running the Thrift Shoppe, the ADL depends on our volunteers to help us find homes for the homeless. Now, the volunteers are stepping up again and helping with a new mission … off-site adoptions. Every weekend the ADL is taking the show on the road to play matchmaker. We are now able to go to more locations that’s to a dedicated group of volunteers who are doing these mobile adoption events themselves! These special volunteers are seeing those happy tails wag as they find their new homes. It’s another way you can help volunteer at the Animal Defense League and we’d love to have even more people joining the team! If you are interested, check out the “Volunteer” section at <a href=\"http://www.adltexas.org\">www.adltexas.org</a> and be sure to register for an orientation class. There is no doubt that seeing a dog or cat find its forever home is a great thing … but to be the one who finds it for them is even more wonderful!','ADL Volunteers: They Don’t Just “Help”','','inherit','open','open','','18-revision-5','','','2012-07-24 09:07:37','2012-07-24 14:07:37','',18,'http://blog.adltexas.org/uncategorized/18-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(4,1,'2012-07-23 22:28:26','2012-07-24 03:28:26','','<< Back to Main Website','','publish','open','open','','main-website','','','2012-07-24 09:10:37','2012-07-24 14:10:37','',0,'http://blog.adltexas.org/?p=4',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(5,1,'2012-07-23 22:30:19','2012-07-24 03:30:19','','Home','','publish','open','open','','httpadltexas-org','','','2012-07-23 22:31:16','2012-07-24 03:31:16','',0,'http://blog.adltexas.org/?p=5',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(6,1,'2012-07-23 22:30:19','2012-07-24 03:30:19','','Our History','','publish','open','open','','our-history','','','2012-07-23 22:31:16','2012-07-24 03:31:16','',0,'http://blog.adltexas.org/?p=6',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(7,1,'2012-07-23 22:30:50','2012-07-24 03:30:50','','Our Staff','','publish','open','open','','our-staff','','','2012-07-23 22:31:16','2012-07-24 03:31:16','',0,'http://blog.adltexas.org/?p=7',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(8,1,'2012-07-23 22:31:17','2012-07-24 03:31:17','','Upcoming Events','','publish','open','open','','upcoming-events','','','2012-07-23 22:31:17','2012-07-24 03:31:17','',0,'http://blog.adltexas.org/?p=8',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(9,1,'2012-07-23 22:32:26','2012-07-24 03:32:26','','Browse Our Pe