og park for our dogs where you can spend 30 minutes (or more) to really get to know one another.  It will make all the difference in the world!  The man who adopted Edison found a real treasure of a dog and I am thrilled for both of them.  You can always check out the adult dogs and cats we have for adoption at <a href=\"http://adltexas.org/category/pets/\">adltexas.org</a>.  There are many more dogs just like Eddie waiting for someone to give them that second look and a second chance.','Give Them a Chance','','publish','open','open','','give-them-a-chance','','','2012-08-24 09:06:18','2012-08-24 14:06:18','',0,'http://blog.adltexas.org/?p=46',0,'post','',0),(47,2,'2012-08-22 09:52:55','2012-08-22 14:52:55','','edison','','inherit','open','open','','edison','','','2012-08-22 09:52:55','2012-08-22 14:52:55','',46,'http://blog.adltexas.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/edison.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(48,2,'2012-08-22 09:54:04','2012-08-22 14:54:04','','edison2','','inherit','open','open','','edison2','','','2012-08-22 09:54:04','2012-08-22 14:54:04','',46,'http://blog.adltexas.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/edison2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(61,2,'2012-08-22 10:04:31','2012-08-22 15:04:31','<img class=\"wp-image-48 alignleft\" title=\"edison2\" src=\"http://blog.adltexas.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/edison2-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"275\" height=\"209\" />One of my favorite dogs here at ADL finally found his forever home yesterday.  Edison had been here since January of this year.  He\'s a beautiful brindle-colored Dutch Shepherd mix with one blue eye.  My husband and I jokingly called him our \"Zombie Apocalypse\" dog because he just looked like the dog who would stick with you through anything.  Edison is one of the best.  He loves to run and play in water but will also just sit with you and relax.  It always made me scrtach my head wondering why he kept getting passed over by adopters.  Actually, that\'s not true ... I think I know exactly